        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>Revision Description</title>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">4700 and 4900 Models added.</emph>
                </para>
                <para></para>
                <para>This TSI applies to models built with Diamond Life&#8482; hydraulic brakes starting January 1,
                    1997.
                </para>
                <para>Effective May, 2005 there are revised recommendations for replacement linings used on Diamond Life
                    hydraulic brakes. These recommendations supersede the information published in TSI-01-04-03.
                </para>
                <para>Vehicles, with Diamond Life brakes, that are under 26,000 GVWR should specify lining HX-402.
                    HX-402 linings are generally used where HX-7A1 linings may have unbalanced or premature wear. HX-402
                    linings became standard production on all vehicles less than 26,000 GVWR on May 2, 2005.
                </para>
                <para>The recommendation for vehicles over 26,000 GVWR is to use HX-7A1 linings which are current
                    production linings. In the past the HX-7A1 lining was susceptible to batch variability, however,
                    each batch is now being verified. Only the verified HX-7A1 linings will be in the PDC's the end of
                    May, 2005.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
